Sentencas: Analytical transmission electron microscopy, in particular with the combination of energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDX) and electron energy-loss spectroscopy (EELS), has been performed to investigate the microstructure and microchemistry of the interfacial region between the cathode (La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3, LSCF) and the electrolyte (Gd-doped ceria, GDC).
Titulo: Two types of diffusions at the cathode/electrolyte interface in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Two types of diffusions, mutual diffusion between cathode and electrolyte as well as the diffusion along grain boundaries, have been clarified.
Titulo: Two types of diffusions at the cathode/electrolyte interface in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: These diffusions suggest that the chemical stability of LSCF and GDC are not as good as previously reported.
Titulo: Two types of diffusions at the cathode/electrolyte interface in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The results are more noteworthy if we take into consideration the fact that such interdiffusions occur even during the sintering process of cell preparation.
Titulo: Two types of diffusions at the cathode/electrolyte interface in IT-SOFCs
